column5: what is he road like going from Hornepayne to Longlac? Are there any service stations, motels, eating places along the way? under normal driving condtions, how long does it take
Road is great, just re-paved a few years ago from Hornepayne to Longlac. Last service station is in Hornepayne. Takes 2.5 hours to reach Longlac
Fill up fuel & food in White River. This will put you in Longlac with plenty of fuel. Good places to eat in White River.

The road is in good shape, be very aware there is very good chance of seeing bear, moose and in June we seen a cougar!. We always stay in Geraldton at the Silver Nugget good room good rate right across from a nice grocery store.
I THINK YOU CAN TAKE WHAT LUV2FISHWALLEYE SAID TO THE BANK HE IS RIGHT ON. WATCH THOSE BEAR AND MOOSE ALSO THE OPP..
